  "prompt": "Is it stealing if you take certain items in your already paid-for hotel room like soap, shampoo, stationery, etc?",
  "response": "Taking items like soap, shampoo, and stationery from your paid-for hotel room is generally not considered stealing. Most hotels expect guests to use and take these small, complimentary items. However, if you take larger items, such as towels, bathrobes, or electronics, this would be considered theft and could result in charges or fines. Always use discretion and consider the hotel's policies regarding what items are meant for guest use and what are not.",
